  'Your tax return shows little or no UK tax.',
  'You are paid under a seafaring contract.',
  'Months at sea and time spent outside the UK.',
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Does claiming the Seafarers Earnings Deduction stop me getting a mortgage?',
    a: 'No. The deduction lowers your UK tax, not your income. Lenders who understand seafarers assess your gross contracted earnings rather than your tax return, so the relief itself is not the obstacle. Lender choice is.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Will I have to give up the deduction to get a mortgage?',
    a: 'No. You keep claiming the Seafarers Earnings Deduction as normal. The right lender simply looks at what you earn under contract instead of the tax figure, so there is no need to change how you file.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Why do some banks misread my income?',
